HEADWORD: Spodumene
<hw>Spod"u*mene</hw> <pr>(sp⟦ocr⟧d"⟦usl⟧*m⟦emac⟧n; 135)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/, p. pr. pass. from <?/ to burn to ashes,
from <grk>spodo`s</grk> ashes; cf. F.
<ets>spodum⟦egrave⟧ne</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral of
a white to yellowish, purplish, or emerald-green color, occurring in
prismatic crystals, often of great size. It is a silicate of alumina and
lithia. See <er>Hiddenite</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spoffish</ent>⟦br⟧
